FW TE Request for TABS AssistanceFYI Original Message From mailto Sent Sunday November AM To Subject TE Request for TABS Assistance November Due to continued unseasonably mild weather and shippers filling contract storage inventories in anticipation of the coming winter heating season Texas Eastern has virtually no storage capacity or linepack available for system operational purposes and cannot continue to absorb imbalances left on the system Pursuant to Section of Rate Schedule TABS Texas Eastern offers to permit TABS Parties to decrease physical receipts of gas into the system by an aggregate quantity of Dthd Any decreases in gas receipts pursuant to Rate Schedule TABS will not reduce such TABS Parties scheduled deliveries whether at a TABS Service Point or city gate markets This request for decreased receipts under TABS is applicable for the STX ETX WLA and ELA TABS Service Points All requests for decreased receipts under Rate Schedule TABS will be accepted on a firstcome firstserved basis After Texas Easterns operational need for decreased receipts has passed Texas Eastern will notify all participating TABS Parties and such parties will have a reasonable time to come back into balance Any TABS party willing to decrease physical receipts into the system should contact their Account Manager NOTE Duke Energy Gas Transmission respects your online time and privacy You have received this email because you elected to subscribe To unsubscribe login to the Email Notification Subscription page at scriptNotificationasp uncheck the appropriate checkbox and click the Submit button

FW TE Critical System WarningFYI Original Message From mailto Sent Sunday November AM To Subject TE Critical System Warning November Texas Eastern Transmission LP Texas Eastern notifies all customers that for the reasons described below scheduled receipts into and deliveries out of the system must match actual receipts into and deliveries out of the system This systemwide warning is issued as a result of actual receipts into the system significantly exceeding actual deliveries Weather in the market area continues to be unseasonably mild and shippers have been filling contract storage inventories in anticipation of the coming winter heating season At this time Texas Easterns storage capacity is approximately full As a result there is virtually no storage capacity or linepack available for system operational purposes and Texas Eastern cannot continue to absorb actual imbalances left on the system Because of the critical nature of this situation and the fact that Texas Eastern no longer has the ability to further absorb imbalances being left on the system Texas Eastern requests that all customers coordinate with their suppliers the actual quantities received into the system to match actual customer takes in the market area If immediate action does not result in reducing the current volume of gas being left on the system Texas Eastern may be forced to issue an operational flow order OFO requiring actual receipts of gas to match actual deliveries out of the system which will be subject to the OFO noncompliance penalty of per dekatherm In addition and as provided for in Texas Easterns FERC Gas Tariff Texas Eastern will take any other actions as may be necessary to protect the integrity of its system including but not limited to suspension of OBAs NOTE Duke Energy Gas Transmission respects your online time and privacy You have received this email because you elected to subscribe To unsubscribe login to the Email Notification Subscription page at scriptNotificationasp uncheck the appropriate checkbox and click the Submit button

FW TE Pipeline Maintenance RevisionMessage From ENRON mailtoIMCEANOTESinfopostdukeenergyEcom NRONcom Sent Friday May PM To Subject TE Pipeline Maintenance Revision May Texas Eastern Transmission TE will have planned maintenance work beginning at AM Tuesday May and ending at AM Thursday May on the discharge of Blessing Compressor Station BLE and on the McAllen line downstream of the Pemex Interconnection PMX TE requests that prior to and during this period to the maximum extent possible shippers ensure that scheduled receipts into the system do not exceed scheduled deliveries out of the system in STX ETX or the system This maintenance will block all gas moving East through Blessing Compressor Station and due to the resulting limited capability to move gas out of STXETX there will be a systematic scheduling required for all receipts between Blessing Station and Fagus Compressor Station FGS on the system beginning at AM on gas day Tuesday May Based on currently scheduled volumes the cuts could have a significant impact on scheduled receipts in the area specified TE strongly recommends TABS parties rank their markets prior to AM Monday Please contact your Operations Account Manager if you have any questions NOTE Duke Energy Gas Transmission respects your online time and privacy You have received this email because you elected to subscribe To unsubscribe login to the Email Notification Subscription page at scriptNotificationasp uncheck the appropriate checkbox and click the Submit button
